ntion in-process unit tests to avoid needing Docker or a server, especially since the user is looking for guidance on the environment/system setup. I can note that no special properties are necessary.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Jackrabbit WebDAV exposes servlet-based server/request APIs and declares javax.servlet:servlet-api as a provided dependency, so generated tests need the servlet API on the test classpath to cover meaningful server-side WebDAV classes.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.servlet:servlet-api:2.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The artifact's WebDAV servlet/request classes depend on javax.servlet types, but the servlet API is declared as provided and is not available from the normal library dependency; the existing test project also adds it explicitly.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image or environment/system property setup appears necessary. Prefer in-process unit coverage of WebDAV methods, XML/property/report parsing, locator factories, and servlet abstractions rather than depending on an external WebDAV server.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The upstream parent declares servlet-api 2.3, while the existing repository test project uses servlet-api 2.4; local Gradle verification remains authoritative if API-version differences matter.\",\n    \"The reported failure is native-image runtime-specific, so deterministic setup alone is unlikely to fix it; metadata or test adjustments may still be required.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0ca44f5ea0f76c3a016a41ea73b6708195a6a74c458e37fb63\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2988, "output": 802, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37582, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite":